Package: nethraops-agent
Version: 0.1.0
Section: admin
Priority: optional
Architecture: all
Depends: python3 (>= 3.11), python3-venv, python3-pip, systemd, curl, ca-certificates
Recommends: jq
Maintainer: NethraOps <engineering@nethraops.com>
Homepage: https://github.com/jithendargolada/mysysteminfo
Description: NethraOps host telemetry agent
 NethraOps agent collects host telemetry (CPU, memory, disk,
 network, processes, containers, log tail) and pushes it to the
 NethraOps platform on a 15 second cadence.
 .
 This package wraps the existing one-line install flow served at
 /install/linux.sh, layering it under standard Debian package
 lifecycle management (apt install / apt upgrade / apt purge,
 systemctl preset, debconf-style pre-seeded config).
 .
 The per-host CLAIM_TOKEN is supplied at install time via
 /etc/nethraops-agent/install.conf (KEY=VALUE) - nothing
 tenant-specific is baked into the package.
